            <bug_when>2011-04-14 08:55:57 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>I&#39;m sorry but thats really not the quality level I would like to have for the framework and for the apps.

- The first part of the toolbar needs to be split up. There is no reason why all buttons included in the first part should be moved in the toolbar together so.

- The order of the buttons in the menu are reversed (most left should be top).

- Buttons for log / html / js can not be deselected which causes inconsistent stats in case someone shows the log in the menu and hides the log in the toolbar.

- Buttons for log / html / js stay disabled if created in a disabled state (e.g. when the start page is openend).

- Use separators in the menu to separate different groups of buttons.</thetext>
